    "\n",
    "- What is `HEAP`?\n",
    "- The heap is where memory lives that you ask for explicitly with malloc() — and you are responsible for giving it back with free().\n",
    "  Heap is a region of memory used for dynamic memory allocation at runtime.\n",
    "\n",
    "  - Allocated manually using malloc(), calloc(), realloc()\n",
    "  - Must be freed manually with free() to avoid memory leaks\n",
    "  - Grows upward in memory (toward higher addresses)\n",
    "  - Opposite end: the stack grows downward\n",
    "\n",
    "  int *p = malloc(sizeof(int));  // allocates on the heap\n",
    "  *p = 42;\n",
    "  free(p);                        // must free manually\n",
    "\n",
    "  Stack vs Heap:\n",
    "\n",
    "  ┌────────────┬────────────────┬─────────────────┐\n",
    "  │            │     Stack      │      Heap       │\n",
    "  ├────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────┤\n",
    "  │ Allocation │ Automatic      │ Manual (malloc) │\n",
    "  ├────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────┤\n",
    "  │ Size       │ Limited        │ Larger          │\n",
    "  ├────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────┤\n",
    "  │ Lifetime   │ Function scope │ Until free()    │\n",
    "  └────────────┴────────────────┴─────────────────┘\n",
    "\n",
    "  Forgetting to free() heap memory = memory leak.\n"
